entries.meaning: (mineralogy) A syenitic rock consisting of microperthite, arfvedsonite, aegirine and, possibly, nepheline.
examples: 1905, John Henry Sears, Essex Institute, The Physical Geography, Geology, Mineralogy and Paleontology of Essex County, Massachusetts (page 213)
The rock-mass in which this umptekite form of hornblende occurs may therefore be called umptekite gabbro.
